  "description": [
    "SCHOOL ITEMS Abe Somers Cheyenne made ten coats from July 20th to the 25th The much needed rain came at last and the lawn once more assumes its natural freshness Maggie Edwards Pueblo died of consump tion on the 3rd inst years of age She was but thirteen The sewingroom tables are receiving a dress of fresh paint in preparation for their line quarters over the new dininghall The main buildings at the Carlisle Indian School arc draped in mourning for the death of our nations best beloved and honored citizen 41 Which Church do you attend The Levigelical 7 was the reply of an In dian boy who does not always get his English straight Mrs Riddall of Williamsport Pa the kin dergarten instructor at the Cherokee Orphan Asylum Indian Territory visited us recently To give our printer boys a chance at camping out in the mountains for health and rest we print but four pages of the Morning Star dur ing July and August The water in the recently renovated cistern by the large boys quarters is most excellent for drinking the boys preferring it to that which comes through the hydrant these warm days _ We are"
